# UI Components

LocalCA uses a modern React component architecture with reusable UI components.

## Key Components

- [components/certificate-details.tsx](mdc:components/certificate-details.tsx) - Displays detailed certificate information
- [components/certificate-table.tsx](mdc:components/certificate-table.tsx) - Table view of certificates with sorting and filtering
- [components/certificate-actions.tsx](mdc:components/certificate-actions.tsx) - Action buttons for certificate operations
- [components/create-certificate-form.tsx](mdc:components/create-certificate-form.tsx) - Form for creating new certificates
- [components/dashboard-header.tsx](mdc:components/dashboard-header.tsx) - Main dashboard header with navigation
- [components/ca-info-card.tsx](mdc:components/ca-info-card.tsx) - Displays CA information
- [components/system-status.tsx](mdc:components/system-status.tsx) - System status information
- [components/settings-tabs.tsx](mdc:components/settings-tabs.tsx) - Settings page tabs
- [components/recent-activity.tsx](mdc:components/recent-activity.tsx) - Recent certificate activity

## UI Component Library

The project uses ShadcnUI, a component library based on Tailwind CSS:

- [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui) - Base UI components
  - Buttons
  - Cards
  - Dialogs
  - Forms
  - Tables
  - Tabs

## Component Usage

- Pages use components to build the UI
- Components are reusable across different pages
- Components follow a consistent design system
- Form components handle validation using React Hook Form and Zod

